A note on the weights, since the question comes up and the repo's own README is
ambiguous about it. Spleeter's README licenses "the code"; the peer-reviewed
JOSS paper by the same authors (Hennequin, Khlif, Voituret & Moussallam, JOSS
5(50):2154, 2020, doi:10.21105/joss.02154) states:

    "Spleeter source code and pre-trained models are available on github and
     distributed under a MIT license."

Deezer trained these models on their own licensed catalogue (the "Bean" dataset)
and released the weights precisely because the training data could not be
released -- so unlike models trained on MUSDB18, there is no non-commercial
dataset term upstream of them. deezer/spleeter#898, asking Deezer to confirm the
weights explicitly, has been open and unanswered since 2024-04-26.
